= SDL_GetNumDisplayModes =
Use this function to return the number of available display modes.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_GetNumDisplayModes(int displayIndex)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''displayIndex'''
|the index of the display to query
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns a number >= 1 on success or a negative error code on failure; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

== Code Examples ==
```c++
You can add your code example here
```

== Remarks ==
The displayIndex needs to be in the range from 0 to [[SDL_GetNumDisplayModes]]() - 1. (0 being the first display/first screen, 1 being the second one etc..) This allows you to supporting multiple screens nicely.

